    <style type="text/css">
        body{
            background-color:cyan
         }

        h1 {
            background-color: gold;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body >
    <h1>Example of Embedded CSS</h1>
    <p>This is an Example of embedded css.In embedded css the style is applied on the whole web page.
        It is done on the head section of the web page. It is also called as internal CSS.
        It will be only applied to this webpage.The styling done in this page will not be reflected on the other pages.
    </p>
    <p  style="background-color: blue;color: white; font-family: Times New Roman, Times, serif;
    font-size: larger;">This is an example of Inline CSS</p>
    <h1 style="background-color:red ;font-family:cursive">Example of Inline CSS</h1>
    <P style="background-color: green; font-size:xx-large; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">This is an example of Inline CSS. 
         Inline css is used to apply a unique style for a specified element. It Overrides any external or embedded style.</P>
</body>

</html>
